# Safety (G-rooted invariants)
# AP-renamed to canonical a,b,c… (the curated 40-formula survey corpus)

Ga  # pure invariant; smallest safety
G(a | b)  # invariant over a boolean guard
G(a -> X b)  # invariant with a next-step obligation (2-step safety)
a & X a  # bounded safety; no fixpoint, finite horizon
G(a -> X a)  # stutter/latch invariant; a former equiv residual
G(a & X a)  # invariant whose body already spans two steps
G((!a & X a) | (a & X !a))  # partscc: alternating terminal SCC; phase-dependent entry (anchor)
G(a <-> X b)  # partscc: 2-step coupled invariant; phase-dependent terminal SCC
